The builtin-fonts configure option was removed, as it at best should
ave been a runtime option. Instead, now it always register all "font
path element" backends, and adds built-ins fonts at the end of the
default font path.
This should be a more reasonable solution, to "correct" the most
common Xorg FAQ (could not open default font 'fixed'), and also don't
break by default applications that use only the standard/historical
X Font rendering.

Backported from trunk:
http://lists.freedesktop.org/archives/xorg/2009-January/042182.html    

--- origsrc/xorg-server-1.5.3/configure.ac	2009-01-18 18:30:38.863875000 -0600
